Cell["\<\
it appears the rule did not work for the first I-Cat. maybe because it\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s odd? i am thinking that for odd numbers we do the same U \
= M/C, but then add 1 (U = M/C + 1). This works for this example.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981135189039809*^9, 3.981135236291901*^9}, {
  3.981135274739338*^9, 3.98113529111344*^9}, {3.9811526348594027`*^9, 
  3.98115264347722*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d44cde50-e729-4262-acbc-\
610be438cc36"],

Cell["so for the first I-Cat, U = 2/1 = 2+1 =3.", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981152553977064*^9, 
  3.981152589823683*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"58c16d0d-3509-4bc9-885b-\
4602ae641176"],

